<h2>Platform Modifiers</h2>
<p>The modifier key combination varies by platform and browser. For an <code>accesskey="s"</code>:</p>

<table>
  <thead><tr><th>Platform</th><th>Modifier</th><th>Full Shortcut</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td>Windows (Chrome, Edge)</td><td><kbd>Alt</kbd></td><td><kbd>Alt+S</kbd></td></tr>
    <tr><td>Windows (Firefox)</td><td><kbd>Alt+Shift</kbd></td><td><kbd>Alt+Shift+S</kbd></td></tr>
    <tr><td>macOS (Chrome, Edge)</td><td><kbd>Ctrl+Alt</kbd></td><td><kbd>Ctrl+Alt+S</kbd></td></tr>
    <tr><td>macOS (Firefox)</td><td><kbd>Ctrl+Alt</kbd></td><td><kbd>Ctrl+Alt+S</kbd></td></tr>
    <tr><td>macOS (Safari)</td><td><kbd>Ctrl+Alt</kbd></td><td><kbd>Ctrl+Alt+S</kbd></td></tr>
    <tr><td>Linux (Chrome)</td><td><kbd>Alt</kbd></td><td><kbd>Alt+S</kbd></td></tr>
    <tr><td>Linux (Firefox)</td><td><kbd>Alt+Shift</kbd></td><td><kbd>Alt+Shift+S</kbd></td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<p>This inconsistency is one of the biggest challenges with <code>accesskey</code>. Users must know their platform's modifier, and documentation must account for all variants.</p>

